sql:
SELECT portfolio_name, performance
FROM portfolios
ORDER BY performance DESC;

SELECT headline
FROM market_news
WHERE news_date = (SELECT MAX(news_date) FROM market_news);

external_knowledge:
Portfolio performance refers to the overall gain or loss in the value of a portfolio due to changes in the value of its constituent stocks; 
Initial value of a portfolio is the total value of all stocks at the time of purchase; 
Current value of a portfolio is the total value of all stocks at the current market price; 
Triggered alerts are notifications sent when the price of a stock crosses a predefined threshold.

